[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     79[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ### What's Done Well
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     80[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     81[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - The five-stage pattern (source → aggregation/feature-engineering → training → forecast storage → consumers) is the right shape and matches industry practice.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     82[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - Step Functions called out as the orchestrator for the multi-step pipeline. Correct choice; the alternatives (cron + Lambda chains, Airflow on MWAA) are heavier or more operational.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     83[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - EventBridge as the cron-equivalent scheduler. Correct.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     84[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - DynamoDB-vs-S3 storage decision explicitly framed by access pattern: "If consumers query forecasts by clinic and date with point lookups, DynamoDB is a great fit. If consumers do bulk analytical queries, write the forecasts to S3 in Parquet and expose them through Athena. Both are valid; the choice depends on how the data gets consumed." This is the right level of nuance for a Simple recipe.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     85[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - SageMaker DeepAR vs. Prophet vs. XGBoost decision framed by data volume and number of series: "For a single clinic with 3+ years of history, classical methods (Prophet, SARIMA, ETS) are an excellent baseline. For dozens or hundreds of related clinics, a global model (DeepAR, gradient-boosted trees on lagged features) often wins because it can learn patterns that transfer between similar clinics." Correct.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     86[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - Lambda or Glue Python Shell called out as alternatives to full Glue Spark for smaller volumes. Correct.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     87[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - Drift detection elevated in "Why This Isn't Production-Ready": "is the rolling 30-day MAE creeping up? Is the prediction interval coverage drifting away from its target? When these alarms fire, retrain. EventBridge can schedule the checks; CloudWatch alarms can fire the alerts." Right level of specificity.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     88[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - Backfill of forecast-vs-actual comparison correctly elevated as a separate job that must run before operations starts trusting the forecast.
