[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    160[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - 70/30 vendor balance: The Problem and The Technology sections (lines 1–76 of the draft, ~3000 words) are entirely vendor-agnostic. AWS service names appear first in the AWS Implementation section. A reader on GCP or Azure walks away having learned about time-series decomposition, classical vs. modern methods, the healthcare-specific failure modes, and the five-stage architecture pattern.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    161[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - CC voice consistent throughout. The opening "It's 6:45 a.m. on a Tuesday. The clinic manager at a 12-provider primary care group is staring at the next two weeks on the schedule and trying to answer a question that should be simple but isn't" lands in the engineer-explaining-something-cool register. The "your brain has built a forecasting model that runs on coffee and pattern recognition" sentence is exactly the right level of self-deprecating expertise.
